<item>
            <title>[LU-8300] unable create .lustre/lost+found/MDTxxxx if lost oi.16.xxx</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8300</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the oi.16.xxx file lost, then the osd_fid_lookup() will return -115 to the LFSCK when try to locate the object for creating &quot;.lustre/lost+found/MDTxxxx&quot;. In fact, we know that such object does not exist, but forget to pass LOC_F_NEW to the OSD. That will cause the LFSCK cannot handle orphan objects under such case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
